# Known-good DEPLOYED binary baseline for `west darling-doctor` check 3.
#
# These are the md5s of the last-known-good deployed closure binaries in the install prefix. The
# doctor compares the deployed dyld (both copies) / mldr / darlingserver against these by default.
#
# Format: one "key = md5" per line; '#' comments. Keys: dyld, mldr, dserver.
# UPDATE this file (and note why + which Bead) whenever a legitimate rebuild changes what is
# deployed — otherwise the doctor will (correctly) flag the new deploy as a baseline mismatch.
#
# Current baseline (2026-07-04, task #116 A0-ARCH stage 3 LANDED): darlingserver updated to
# the A0-ARCH stage 3 landing (commit 78d7f7b + fixes 2d2cd37/5020b3f/e66aeee, fix-2 ccbe517
# reverted by 1789d62; binary d81b5cf1): interrupt-as-cancellation -- the interrupted call
# unwinds via NORMAL dispatch on its own fiber (frame armed {cancellationArmed,replyOwed,
# enterCall}; enter's doneWorking restores+reparks "repark-interrupt-cancel"; the cancel wake
# is KEPT as the dispatch vehicle; the enter reply is deferred to reply-stash time). DELETED:
# jumpToResume, the syscall-return/microthread setcontext detours, and cross-frame savedStack
# free -- so the #114 SEGV stack-borrowing crash class is GONE (zero interrupt SEGVs across
# every stage-3 run). Branch fix/a0-arch-redesign, see tests/A0-ARCH-STAGE3.md. Acceptance:
# quick gate 19/19 gating green (nestwait 8/8, brew xz 2/2 strict, both storm known-limit legs
# OK), ZERO mstate/xwait violations, ZERO SEGV; synth 16/16; cvstorm2-throttled (#114 grain)
# 12/12 OK at full storm rate. KNOWN, PRE-EXISTING (proven by A/B vs 7692d9f6, NOT stage-3
# regressions, re-scoped out): (a) cvstorm2-flood coin-flip HANG = dispatch starvation gated to
# the 1Hz XNU long-term-timer scan (task #118); (b) rare ~2% nestwait semaphore_timedwait -111
# (-ECONNREFUSED on RPC #62) flake, seen pre-stage-3 (PERF25A census). dyld/mldr unchanged.
#   dyld    79b22273  (dyld-733.6, boot-compatible with the deployed 06-15 closure)
#   mldr    f0cd2a82  (perf#21b compact-fd band)
#   dserver d81b5cf1  (ring + A0 a3de8c2 + A0-ARCH stages 0/1 + 2a/2b/2c + stage 3 interrupt-as-cancellation)
# Previous dserver baselines: 7692d9f6 (2c, .bak in darling-prefix/bin), 47ac175d (2b, .bak),
# e50a3450 (2a), a889e85f (stage 1, .bak), 886d13af (a3de8c2, task #113).

dyld    = 79b22273481ea61ab63c0606c23ab300
